-- Obama Plans to Nominate Diplomat James Jeffrey as U.S. Ambassador to Iraq
-- Nicholas Johnston
-- 2010-06-25T22:59:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/obama-plans-to-nominate-diplomat-james-jeffrey-as-u-s-ambassador-to-iraq.html

          
          
             President  Barack Obama  intends to
nominate career diplomat  James Jeffrey  as the U.S. ambassador to
Iraq, the White House said.  
 Jeffrey, currently the U.S. envoy to Turkey, has previously
worked as a deputy national security adviser to President  George W. Bush  and as principal deputy assistant Secretary of State for
Near Eastern affairs. In 2004 and 2005, he was U.S. charge
dâ€™affairs in Iraq and the deputy chief of mission in Baghdad.  
 The post, which requires Senate confirmation, is currently
held by  Christopher Hill , another career foreign service
officer.  
